column5: Here's 5 of about 25 or 30 of my biggest Smallies from today, Bass Magnet Tubes & Bass Magnet Senko imitators, water temp was 75 degrees, caught between 3' & 18'    Randy & Moe kept a few of there Smallies mostly caught on Tubes   The Fishing GODS must be watching over us Richard
75 degrees!!!???  Holy shoot!  what a difference 5-7hours south makes!!!??
Fish'n around the out flow from the hydro plant at Bruce Richard
1st look at the Randy and Moe video still (without playing it) shows a couple of guys in float suits, standing in front of a nice ice float. It must be winter up there already!

HAHA I had 2 Cameras & the 1st ones battery died so Moe took my video with a different camera, we all had floater suits on but I got hot, it was very cool in the morning & was calling for rain, we ran a few miles out in Lake Huron just being safe & that is foam floating in front of Randy's boat, water temp was 61 degrees in the bay & 75 degrees by the Hydro out flow Richard
